adviseScripts.text: Commander, if you could only choose one...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Which do you prefer: dogs or cats?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I prefer dogs.
I'm more fond of cats.
I see. So you are a dog person, not a cat person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Dogs are quite adorable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I am fond of cats as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: They may not look like it, but actually they're pretty sad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: That's why I want to shower them with as much love as possible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I talk to Admi about animals.
Because of Privaty and me, Yulha ended up overworking herself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm quite concerned about her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything I can do to help her out?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Just say 'Thank you.' She would appreciate that.
Tell her you'll help her with her work from now on.
Say 'Thank you'?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I imagine she would be pretty embarrassed to hear me say that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But, you're right. I really should say it to her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: That was very helpful. Thank you very much, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Hm... I think Yulha would be furious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: She'd probably tell me to just worry about doing my own job instead of messing with hers.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But, thank you anyway. I'll take it into consideration.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Admi about Yulha.
... Privaty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: When will she ever grow up?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It'd be better if you just gave up on that idea.
Someday, she will. Someday...
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: So, it is just wishful thinking... It will never happen.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Thank you, Commander. Letting go of false hope makes me feel much better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Right. Someday...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh*
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I pat Admi's back to show some moral support.
The Outpost is such a weird place.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It's smaller than average, but we have a police station and a courthouse.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: We have a hospital and a train station, too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: What's your favorite place in the Outpost, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: The Commander's Room.
The courthouse, because it's where you are.
Oh... I like it, too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Because that's where I can see you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Oh, really? Thank you, Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm quite glad you feel that way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time talking about the Outpost with Admi.
Commander, what kind of weather do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Sunny skies.
Rainy days.
I see. Sunshine really does seem to make you happy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It's the perfect weather for having fun outside.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I feel the same way. You know how hard combat can be
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: on a rainy day... But, I do enjoy hearing the sound of the rain.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: The melody of rain helps me cope with my loneliness.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Admi about the weather.
Commander, we are under the command of the Central Government.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: We must treat their orders as our top priority.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Are there times when that makes you feel sad, or even hateful toward us?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Yes, there are times.
Never.
I knew it. That's entirely normal.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But, Commander, you have been always so sincere and kind to us. Thank you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Thank you for staying true to us.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Even if you are not really being honest, thank you for saying that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I spend some more quality time with Admi.
Commander, do you have an ideal type?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Someone who is mature.
Someone who is cute.
Oh, is that so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It is physically impossible for me to look mature.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I... understand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Then, I guess I'm lucky to look like this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm not saying I'm cute, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: ... I feel that if I work hard, I can be closer to the kind of woman you like.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I talk to Admi about ideal types.
People always say that no love lasts forever...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Do you agree with that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Eternal love does exist.
Eternal love is a lie.
I knew you would say that, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: To be honest, I'm also hoping that such a love really exists.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: ... Thank you, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: So, Commander, you feel the same as everyone else...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Even so, I always like to think it might be real.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But... I don't know. Maybe it's not...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation about love with Admi.
Commander, where do you go when you want to relax and unwind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Downtown, somewhere crowded.
A park without too many people.
Ah... You like places with a lot of people.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: When I go to crowded places, I get tired very quickly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But there are plenty of things to keep you entertained downtown. Maybe, that's why you like it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I also enjoy quiet places with very few people.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I feel at peace.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Perhaps, when I want to relax, I'll go to the same place as you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Admi about places to relax.
They say that to have peace of mind, having a hobby is important.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm thinking of getting one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: But... I'm not quite sure what kind of hobby to choose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: What about looking at cat pictures? Or taking cat pictures?
What about exercising?
Pictures of cats?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: That sounds nice. I will start today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Working out might be too hard for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It would feel too much like training.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Oh! I'm sorry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Let... let me think about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Admi about hobbies.
Every beginning has an end.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: If everything is bound to end, then why bother trying?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: What are your thoughts, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: You just need to start fresh.
I can't give up, not until I know how it all ends.
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Even if you start something new, it will end eventually.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Don't you find the repetition exhausting?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It's a little hard to understand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: How it all ends...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I suppose you could define "end" in various ways.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Surely one of those definitions must include a happy ending.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: That seems like a good mindset.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I have a nice heart-to-heart.
I wanted to get Yulha something for always working so hard.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Any ideas?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: A vacation.
Some alcohol.
Yulha would never go for that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: If she relaxed for even a minute, she'd fall behind in her work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm grateful for what she does, but I feel a little bad for her too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It's not good to rely on alcohol,
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: but it's probably the only way she can get outside of her head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the suggestion!
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I talk about Yulha.
What type of music do you typically listen to, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Subdued and solemn music.
Upbeat and exciting music.
I like that kind of music too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Sitting in the park and listening to music puts me at ease.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Would you like to come with me some time?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I tend to prefer more subdued music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: However, if you can recommend me some more upbeat music, I'd love to hear it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I talk about our taste in music.
I've been having a lot of nightmares lately, so mornings have been tough.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Do you dream often?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Yes, all the time.
No, not very often.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Does that not wear you out mentally?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I hope you at least have good dreams.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad to hear that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Dreaming a lot when you sleep can be pretty taxing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It's nice to hear that you sleep soundly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I discuss dreams.
Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: If we manage to reclaim the surface, how would you feel?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'd be elated.
I'm not sure how I'd feel.
I knew you would feel that way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I would be happy too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I hope that day will come soon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Oh, is that so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I thought for sure you'd be happy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: It seems that there's still a lot I don't know about you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I discuss the surface and its future.
Commander, are you any good at claw machines?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: There's one in front of the convenience store.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I tried it several times but can't seem to grab anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm the claw machine master.
Honestly, I'm not very good.
Is that true?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Can you come with me next time then?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'll buy you a tasty treat afterward.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: That's too bad...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Guess I just need to practice some more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: When I get good enough, I'll be sure to snag something for you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I talked about claw machines.
Have you tried any of the food up on the surface?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I tried grapes for the first time a few days ago.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I've never tasted anything so sweet.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I've eaten a lot.
I've barely tried anything.
What did you find the most memorable?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: If I ever have the opportunity, I'd like to try some different things.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Although it'd taste even better if you and I could eat it together...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: No kidding...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I thought you would have tried all sorts of stuff.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: If I come across any more, I'll make sure to invite you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I talk about food up on the surface.
Commander, out of curiosity, is there anything you would like as a gift?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Your time.
A cat doll.
M-my time?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Well... you can have it anytime.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Um...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Are you sure that's what you want?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: You don't need to be so considerate of me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I talk about gifts.
There were a lot of books about cats at the library.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I ended up borrowing 6 books all at once.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I may have gone a bit overboard.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Just a tad.
Not at all, as long as you finish reading all of them.
I don't know when I'll find time to read them all...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: There may be other people waiting to read them as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I better go return a few of them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: You're right, but I don't know when I'll find time to read them all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: ... But thank you for putting a positive spin on all this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'll try to read them as fast as I can.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I have a back and forth about the books she borrowed.
Cats are so adorable when they meow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: How do they make that sound, I wonder?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: *Meow*
Not as cute as your voice.
Hmmph.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Your voice is too deep, it doesn't sound like a cat at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Can you try again?
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: ...Oh, thank you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: This is the first time I've been complimented about my voice...
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: I'm a little embarrassed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Admi

adviseScripts.text: Admi and I get into the nitty-gritty about cats and their meows.
